<div class="container">
    <h1 class="text-center">Client-Side Communication</h1>

    <div class="beginner-note">
        <div class="beginner-note-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-desktop"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="beginner-note-content">
            <h4>Think of Client-Side Like Your Brain Processing Information</h4>
            <p><strong>Client-Side = Happens in YOUR device</strong></p>
            <p><strong>Simple analogy:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>You receive a recipe (HTML/CSS/JavaScript from server)</li>
                <li>You follow the recipe in your kitchen (your browser)</li>
                <li>You mix ingredients, bake, and decorate (client-side processing)</li>
                <li>The final cake appears on your counter (your screen)</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>In web terms:</strong> Client-side means work happens in YOUR browser/device!</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="intro-section">
        <p><strong>Client-side communication</strong> refers to everything that happens in your browser or device after receiving data from a server. It's like your computer's brain processing information!</p>
        
        <div class="alert alert-info">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Quick Definition:</strong> Client-side = <strong>work done by YOUR device</strong>, not the server.
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">Client-Side vs Server-Side: The Big Picture</h2>
    
    <div class="comparison-diagram">
        <div class="comparison-side client-side-comp">
            <div class="side-header">
                <i class="fas fa-laptop"></i>
                <h3>Client-Side</h3>
                <div class="side-badge">Your Device</div>
            </div>
            <div class="side-features">
                <div class="feature">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i>
                    <span>Happens in browser</span>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i>
                    <span>Uses HTML, CSS, JavaScript</span>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i>
                    <span>Immediate feedback</span>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i>
                    <span>Can work offline</span>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <i class="fas fa-times text-danger"></i>
                    <span>Limited to browser capabilities</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="comparison-vs">
            <div class="vs-circle">VS</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="comparison-side server-side-comp">
            <div class="side-header">
                <i class="fas fa-server"></i>
                <h3>Server-Side</h3>
                <div class="side-badge">Remote Server</div>
            </div>
            <div class="side-features">
                <div class="feature">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i>
                    <span>Happens on server</span>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i>
                    <span>Uses Python, C#, Java, etc.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i>
                    <span>Processes data securely</span>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <i class="fas fa-check text-success"></i>
                    <span>Access to databases</span>
                </div>
                <div class="feature">
                    <i class="fas fa-times text-danger"></i>
                    <span>Requires internet connection</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">What Happens Client-Side? Real Examples</h2>
    
