    <div class="ajax-explanation">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-sync"></i> AJAX: The Magic Behind Live Updates</h3>
        
        <div class="ajax-flow">
            <div class="ajax-step">
                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h5>You Scroll Twitter</h5>
                    <p>You reach bottom of your feed</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="ajax-arrow">→</div>
            
            <div class="ajax-step">
                <div class="step-number">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h5>JavaScript Sends Request</h5>
                    <p>Browser asks: "More tweets please!"</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="ajax-arrow">→</div>
            
            <div class="ajax-step">
                <div class="step-number">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h5>Server Responds</h5>
                    <p>Sends new tweets (JSON data)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="ajax-arrow">→</div>
            
            <div class="ajax-step">
                <div class="step-number">4</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h5>JavaScript Updates Page</h5>
                    <p>Adds new tweets WITHOUT refreshing!</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="ajax-code">
            <div class="code-header">JavaScript AJAX Example</div>
            <div class="code-content">
<pre><code class="language-javascript">
// Client-side JavaScript code
fetch('https://api.twitter.com/more-tweets')
  .then(response => response.json())
  .then(data => {
    // Add new tweets to page WITHOUT refreshing
    data.tweets.forEach(tweet => {
      document.querySelector('#feed')
        .appendChild(createTweetElement(tweet));
    });
  });

// Page doesn't reload! Magic!
</code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="real-time-demo">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Live Demo: Client-Side Timer</h3>
        
        <div class="demo-container">
            <div class="timer-display">
                <div class="timer" id="clientTimer">00:00</div>
                <div class="timer-controls">
                    <button class="btn btn-success" id="startTimer">
                        <i class="fas fa-play"></i> Start
                    </button>
                    <button class="btn btn-warning" id="pauseTimer">
                        <i class="fas fa-pause"></i> Pause
                    </button>
                    <button class="btn btn-danger" id="resetTimer">
                        <i class="fas fa-redo"></i> Reset
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="demo-explanation">
                <p><strong>This timer runs entirely client-side!</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>No server communication needed</li>
                    <li>JavaScript handles all timing logic</li>
                    <li>Runs even if you disconnect from internet</li>
                    <li>All processing happens in YOUR browser</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="benefits-limitations">
        <div class="benefits">
            <h4><i class="fas fa-thumbs-up"></i> Benefits of Client-Side</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Fast:</strong> Immediate responses</li>
                <li><strong>Responsive:</strong> Smooth user experience</li>
                <li><strong>Offline capable:</strong> Some features work offline</li>
                <li><strong>Reduced server load:</strong> Less work for servers</li>
                <li><strong>Interactive:</strong> Rich user interfaces</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="limitations">
            <h4><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Limitations</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Browser dependent:</strong> Different browsers behave differently</li>
                <li><strong>Security:</strong> Code is visible to users</li>
                <li><strong>Performance:</strong> Limited by user's device</li>
                <li><strong>No data processing:</strong> Can't access databases directly</li>
                <li><strong>SEO challenges:</strong> Search engines may not see dynamic content</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="interactive-quiz">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-brain"></i> Client-Side or Server-Side?</h3>
        
        <div class="quiz-questions">
            <div class="quiz-item">
                <p>Validating that an email address is in the correct format when typing</p>
                <div class="quiz-options">
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-primary quiz-btn" data-correct="true">Client-Side</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-primary quiz-btn" data-correct="false">Server-Side</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-feedback"></div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="quiz-item">
                <p>Checking if a username already exists in the database</p>
                <div class="quiz-options">
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-primary quiz-btn" data-correct="false">Client-Side</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-primary quiz-btn" data-correct="true">Server-Side</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-feedback"></div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="quiz-item">
                <p>Animating a button when you hover over it</p>
                <div class="quiz-options">
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-primary quiz-btn" data-correct="true">Client-Side</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-outline-primary quiz-btn" data-correct="false">Server-Side</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-feedback"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="key-points">
        <h3>Key Points to Remember</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Client-side = Your device</strong> - Processing happens in browser</li>
            <li><strong>Technologies:</strong> HTML, CSS, JavaScript</li>
            <li><strong>Fast & responsive:</strong> Immediate user feedback</li>
            <li><strong>AJAX:</strong> Update pages without refreshing</li>
            <li><strong>Benefits:</strong> Speed, interactivity, offline capability</li>
            <li><strong>Limitations:</strong> Browser differences, security concerns</li>
            <li><strong>Works with server-side:</strong> They complement each other!</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("HttpPart2", "WebCommunication")" class="btn btn-outline-primary ajax-link">← HTTP Part 2</a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("ServerSide", "WebCommunication")" class="btn btn-primary ajax-link">Next: Server-Side Communication →</a>
    </div>
</div>

